<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_7fsad"
    xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>ᵆfsad</orth></form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>æfsad</orth></form>
    <sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>войско</q>
        </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>troop</q>
        </cit></sense>
    <re><form type="lemma"><orth>fsæddon</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation"
                    xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>войсковой</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>of a troop</q>
                </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>военный</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>military</q>
                </cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                    <q>воин</q>
                </cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                    <q>warrior</q>
                </cit></sense></sense></re>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>spada-</w></mentioned> (с
        обычной метатезой %isp%i → %ifs%i). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
            ><lang/><w>sipāh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>spāh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru">(из перс.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Persian)
                </note><w>spah</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*aspāδ
                (ʽsp’δ)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>spādā-,
            spāδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>spāda-</w><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в собственном имени %iTaxmaspāda-%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (in a proper name %iTaxmaspāda-%i)</note></mentioned>.
        Налично в нескольких %bскифских%b собственных именах: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"
                ><lang/><w>Σπαδακος, Σπαδαγας, ʽΑμωσπαδος</w></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>182</biblScope></bibl>). На основании этих имен
        можно считать несомненным существование в %bскифском%b слов <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"
                ><lang/><w>σπαδ- (spāda-)</w></mentioned> и <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"
                ><lang/><w>σπαδακ-, σπαδαγ- (spādaka)</w></mentioned>; последнее слово могло
        означать ‘воин’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 60, III
                81</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope
                xml:lang="ru">64, 182, 212 сл., 527</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">64, 182, 212
                ff., 527</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>spada-</w></mentioned>
        (with the usual metathesis %isp%i → %ifs%i). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>sipāh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"
            ><lang/><w>spāh</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><note type="comment"
                xml:lang="ru">(из перс.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(from Persian)
                </note><w>spah</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*aspāδ
                (ʽsp’δ)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>spādā-,
            spāδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>spāda-</w><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="ru"> (в собственном имени %iTaxmaspāda-%i)</note><note
                type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (in a proper name %iTaxmaspāda-%i)</note></mentioned>.
        It is present in some %bScythian%b proper names: <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"
                ><lang/><w>Σπαδακος, Σπαδαγας, ʽΑμωσπαδος</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>182</biblScope></bibl>). Based on these names, the
        existence of the words <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>σπαδ- (spāda-)</w></mentioned>
        and <mentioned xml:lang="xsc"><lang/><w>σπαδακ-, σπαδαγ- (spādaka)</w></mentioned> in
        %bScythian%b can be considered undoubted; the latter word might have meant
                ‘warrior’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 60, III
                81</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
                /><biblScope>31</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope
                xml:lang="ru">64, 182, 212 сл., 527</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">64, 182, 212
                ff., 527</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
